
[1]diligence

   DILIGENCE, n. [L., to love earnestly; to choose.]

   1. Steady application in business of any kind; constant effort to
   accomplish what is undertaken; exertion of body or mind without
   unnecessary delay or sloth; due attention; industry; assiduity.

   Diligence is the philosophers stone that turns every thing to gold.

   Brethren, give diligence to make your calling and election sure. 2
   Peter 1.

   2. Care; heed; heedfulness.

   Keep thy heart with all diligence. Proverbs 4.

   3. The name of a stage-coach, used in France.
